As shown in Table 3, 1.36 fg/μL genomic DNA was both detected by S. Enteritidis real-time quantitative PCR detection system and Salmonella spp. Besides, the two systems could detect 2.49 CFU/mL S. Enteritidis cells without enrichment (Table 4
                        ). As for the two systems to the plasmid sensitivity (Table 5
                        ). Briefly, 11.6 copies/μL plasmid containing the Gene ID:1828390769 target gene could be detected by the S. Enteritidis system, whereas 1.08 copies/μL plasmid containing Gene ID:3335471 could be detected for the Salmonella spp. detection system.
